    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-08-20T19:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-08-20T19:30:00-05:00" n="37"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>37. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Poland</gloss>
                    <note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d37fn0">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 611.93/8–1858. Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_LLR1"
                            >Lutkins</persName>, cleared with EE, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>. Repeated to Bern and
                        Geneva.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1958-08-20T20:30:00-04:00">August 20, 1958, 8:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. Warsaw for <persName corresp="#p_BJD1">Beam</persName>; Bern for <persName
                        corresp="#p_CRN1">Clough</persName>; Geneva for Dexter. Your 234.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d37fn1">Telegram 234 from Warsaw, August 20, requested guidance
                        concerning plans for <persName corresp="#p_BJD1">Beam</persName>’s initial
                        meeting with <persName>Wang</persName>. (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Ibid.</hi>)</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Especially in view present tension situation Taiwan Straits Department
                        considers desirable talks be renewed with minimum delay following Chinese
                        Communists response. Concur your plan arrange earliest feasible initial
                        meeting (i.e. before departure Vienna) if <persName>Wang</persName> replies
                        this week. In event response made after your departure suggest Embassy
                        inform you in Vienna and you then instruct Embassy arrange date soon after
                        your return notifying Dexter accordingly. In this case would be desirable
                        you plan return on basis minimum period after September 7 considered
                        necessary for inspection fair exhibition.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Injunction para 2 <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 97<note n="2"
                            xml:id="d37fn2">Telegram 97 to Warsaw, July 30, stated that alternate
                            use of the two Embassies was ruled out for policy reasons. (<hi
                                rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> 611.93/7–2858)</note> applies with as much
                        or greater force to presence United States representative in Chinese
                        Communist Embassy as to reverse. No calls should be made at Chinese
                        Communist Embassy; even initial contact should be made at 3rd country
                        embassy or other suitable neutral locale.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Not considered you require any credentials other than letter July 28 to
                            <persName>Wang</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_MEW1"
                            >Martin</persName> our previously designated representative.<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d37fn3">See <ref target="#d18fn1">footnote 1, Document
                            18</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">Herter</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
